other_tests.findings: No focal or textural hepatic abnormalities identified; no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Common bile duct measures up to approximately 4 mm. No stones in the gallbladder. Small amount of gallbladder wall edema; no evidence of gallbladder distention. Main portal vein demonstrates normal hepatopetal flow. Evaluation of the pancreas is limited. Spleen measures approximately 13.8 cm, upper limits of normal.
